So, what will be the long term effect? I propose this:<br>
<br>
1. Those that choose Clerics are the ones that are interested in grouping - keeping the group members alive through their skill at healing and playing an important role on raids (these aren't all the reasons but some I'm sure).<br>
2. Making the Cleric class better at soloing and DRU and SHM better at healing will decrease the appeal of Clerics in favor of DRU and SHM which are also great group classes but also have a lot more utility.<br>
3 Over time, attrition will slowly decrease the number of Clerics in-game and slowly thin out the crowd that can rez others, which is one of the most important in-game abilities.<br>
4. Pretty soon we are back at a bottleneck in the high end game only we are stuck with not enough people to rezz. What then, give rezz to DRU/SHM as has already been suggested?<br>
<br>
Seems like VI in &quot;balancing&quot; the classes is balancing more and more towards classes that are pretty much the same with a couple class-defining spells. I for one would like to go back to where each class had it's own specific area of expertice and doesn't overlap. Instead of adding more spells and abilities, take some away. Sure people would cry a bit, but it's a matter of fixing the long term problems. Take away anything higher than GH from SHM and DRU, remove the Rezz from Necros, Give stuns to Paladin only, Take away some nukes from DRU and the Shaman pet as well as Torpor etc. Make each class good at only a couple things and not able to do the others. This idea of eveyone can do everything but only a couple things really well is BS. Of course every class want's to have the cake and eat it too, and some have gotten close to getting it (DRU/SHM) but if that's going to be the case, just distill the game to a few classes - WAR, Priest, Wizard, Theif, Monk and Bard like the old Bard's Tale and be done with it.<br>
And don't get me started with the caster armor that is nearly as much AC as tank armor.<br>
Vulrath<br>
